{
  "number": 2038,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2038",
  "title": "How can a widget prevent an initial search?",
  "body": "I know I can control the initial search using the [searchFunction](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/documentation/#hide-results-on-init) option.\r\n\r\nWhat I'm wondering is if it is possible for a widget itself to somehow tap into this functionality.\r\n\r\nUse-case is a widget that plots pins on a map. I want to delay in the initial search until I have the map bounds available. This can be achieved like so:\r\n\r\n```\r\noptions.searchFunction = function(helper) {\r\n  if (helper.getQueryParameter('insideBoundingBox')) {\r\n    helper.search();\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, I'd ideally like to bake this functionality into the widget itself if possible. So if my map widget was added to the instantsearch, the initial search would be blocked, without having to override `options.searchFunction`.\r\n\r\nIf it is possible, please clue me in. If not, I suppose this is a PR.",
